Device: Kindle DX, Yotaphone 2, iPhone7+, Dasung 13.3" HD-FT Monitor, iPad Pro**How much did you pay for the Mira Pro?**

* * *

 The upcoming Dasung 253 is suppose to be ~$2,500.

 I heard the Mira Pro is under $2,000.

 As the Mira Pro does not have touchscreen support, this may be a deal-breaker for me, as sometimes using a mouse on an e-ink screen is challenging. With my finger, I know exactly what I'm "clicking on", as well when needing to pinch-and-zoom, it would be a hassle to then have to bounce back to the LCD screen (of the laptop or desktop), then back to the e-ink monitor.
